"Everything is a file" in Unix and its derivatives.
Use command ls  (ls -- list directory contents)
ls -la (shows dot file -- hidden files or config files)
d:The file type
rwx:The permissions that the owner has over the file
rwx:The permissions that the group has over the file
rwx:The permissions that all the other users have over the file
Pipes and redirection: connect multiple commands together
cat rabbit | hexdump
hexdump: a tool that shows the hex value for each character
cat rabbit | hexdump -C
hex "0a": new line character
Be familiar with Hex you going to use it a lot!!
man ascii
